cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a new algorithm for incorporating class conditional information into the discriminator of GANs, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm on various datasets, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE) and graphics (cs.GR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.NE and cs.GR.
